On the eve of the referendum a spokeswoman for the “la vox maltais” said – “We have big challenges in family life, divorce and all sorts of issues. We need to do something about this. We have to reaffirm family and human life through this referendum”.

Female MP Dr Dolores Cristina said: “As a party we are very clear on the place of a foetus within life, as a human being and an heir of God. Our duty will be to protect human life and to uphold the dignity of woman. In supporting such a law one is not negating the right of the woman to choose”.

I wonder…

All this comes on a week where Denmark is about to legalise euthanasia for children. According to the country’s Health Ministry – “Under the proposal, parents and doctors could agree that children should be allowed to die – if the child is reported to be extremely ill and expected to die within a short time… It will not be up to the parents to choose euthanasia on behalf of their children.”

Euthanasia is supported by 80% of Danes due to the ‘best interests’ of the child argument. They have also had access to painkilling drugs for years anonymously. Most people in favour of legalising euthanasia in the UK support this
